==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Fives
<hw>Fives</hw> <pr>(f⟦imac⟧vz)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos> <def>A kind of
play with a ball against a wall, resembling tennis; -- so named because
three <xex>fives</xex>, or <xex>fifteen</xex>, are counted to the
game.</def> <rj><au>Smart.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Fives court</b></col>, <cd>a place for playing
fives.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fives</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Fives
<hw>Fives</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Vives</er>.]</ety> <def>A
disease of the glands under the ear in horses; the vives.</def>
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>five-spot</ent>⟦br⟧
